# 8. 結婚式と同じくらい

Minori: Alright, so...
Minori: That's it for today's episode of Walking with Minori brought to you from the Phoenix Bridal Fair!
Minori: Actually, this one went on for so long that it felt like a special feature...
Minori: Anyway, what did you guys think? Did you all have fun?
Comments: <That was way too much fun! Time really flew by!> <I really enjoyed getting to learn more about you and your friends, Minori!> <I wish I could've gone today! I'm definitely going tomorrow!>
Nene: Thank goodness... Looks like they enjoyed everything.
Comments: <I really enjoyed your segment, Nene!> <You should come visit again soon.> <Awesome show, Nene!>
Nene: Oh...
Nene: Hehe. Thanks... I'm a little embarrassed, but also really happy.
Minori: Oh, Nene, that reminds me!
Minori: Thank you so much again for helping me when I forgot my line during that scene!
Nene: Th-There's no need to thank me.
Nene: I mean, I know what it feels like to draw a blank at a crucial moment...
Minori: You do?
Nene: Yes, all too well...
Nene: While we're on the subject, Hanasato, I was really impressed by the way you were able to go along with my ad-libbing.
Nene: And I should take this opportunity to also thank you.
Nene: Your singing and dancing really made everyone smile in the end.
Nene: Next time, I'd like for you to see one of our shows as a member of the audience. We promise to make it an unforgettable experience.
Minori: Nene...
Minori: Thanks!
Minori: Anyway, we'll have to end things here! Make sure to tune in next time!
Nene: Bye bye!
Minori: Just gotta make sure I hit the “End Stream” button and... Okay, that's a wrap!
Nene: *Sigh* Thank goodness we made it through...
Minori: Hehe. Thanks again for everything you did today, Nene! Oh!
Shiho: Nice work today, you two.
Minori: Hi, you guys!
Minori: I-I'm really sorry about the show! After I promised to see it with all of you!
Nene: Oh, right! I need to apologize. Please don't blame Hanasato for what happened...
Ena: There's no need to apologize. We figured that she had a good reason.
Honami: Between how fun your performance was, Hanasato, and you magically changing into that dress, Kusanagi, everyone in the audience really seemed to enjoy themselves.
Nene: Really? That's good to hear...
Ena: Oh, that reminds me. This is sorta unrelated, but...
Ena: I took a video of the show since it was okay for us to record.
Ena: And I was wondering if you could use it for one of your MMJ streams.
Minori: Huh?
Minori's Voice: <So, let me take this opportunity to show you an example of a fun live house wedding!>
Minori's Voice: <Everyone! It's time to start the Happy Wedding Concert!>
Minori: Wow, you took such an amazing video!
Honami: It's so steady, and the sound's crystal clear. I'm sure Hanasato will have an easy time commentating.
Ena: See what I mean? You can even see everyone's faces really clearly, so it felt like a shame for me to just hog it.
Ena: Also, it's not every day that we get to see you sing and act on stage like this. I'm sure it'll be fun for all of you to discuss it as a group.
Minori: Y-Yeah!
Minori: So, Nene! Would it be okay for us to use this video for one of our streams?
Nene: I'd have to ask Ms. Nozaki, but I'm pretty sure that there won't be any problems.
Nene: If anything, she'll probably want you to use it. Lemme give her a quick call.
Minori: Oh, thank you so much!
Nene: Okay, thank you.
Nene: Thank goodness I was able to get permission. I need to tell Hanasato right away...
Luka: <Nice work today, Nene♪>
Nene: Oh, Luka!
Luka: <I saw everything in secret. I was so glad to see both your show and stream go as well as they did♪>
Nene: Thanks... Me too.
Nene: Still, I really got to experience a lot today. Working part-time here, doing that stream, holding a talk segment...
Luka: <Hehe...>
Luka: <Then, this day must've filled you with so much joy. Like it was your own wedding day♪>
Nene: Oh...
Nene: You might be right. It was a pretty packed day.
Luka: <See what I mean?>
Luka: <Still, I like the idea of being the bride on her wedding day...>
Luka: <I might just ask the others if we can do a show about a wedding after I get back.>
Nene: Yeah, we should do a show about one in SEKAI sometime.
Nene: Sorry for the wait... Huh? Where are Mochizuki and the others?
Minori: Oh, they said they had plans afterwards, so they had to leave! But they asked me to thank you for everything that happened today, Nene.
Nene: Okay. Oh, Hanasato, I got permission from Ms. Nozaki. You and your group can use that video for a stream.
Minori: Really?! Thank you so much! I promise to make good use of it!
Minori: Anyway, why don't we both go get changed and head home?
Nene: Wait, umm... Together? I probably have to go help clean up and stuff...
Minori: That's okay! I can wait!
Minori: Oh, uhh, but I don't wanna cause you any trouble!
Nene: N-No, you won't be... If anything, I...
Minori: Huh?
Nene: Uhh... I'm really glad you asked...
Minori: Y-You are?! Thank goodness!
Minori: While we're at it, we should get something to eat! There's a really yummy-looking place just over there!
Nene: Oh, that'd be nice. I've been working since this morning, so I could probably eat a horse right now.
Minori: Me too! Then, let's hurry and get changed!
Minori: Nooo...! Th-The hem of this dress is so long! I keep stepping on it!
Nene: Hehe. Oh, Hanasato. Be careful not to trip over it, okay?
Minori: Hehe. Okay!
